properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 6:30PM CST until January 14 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY FOR SNOW AND ICE THIS EVENING AND
TONIGHT...

.Two to four inches of snow is expected tonight in west central
Wisconsin. The heavier accumulation will likely occur along the I-
94 corridor, and along and east of Highway 53. The accumulating
snow should end after midnight to the east, but some patchy
freezing drizzle could remain for a time after the snow ends.

A light glazing of ice from patchy freezing drizzle is possible
across southern Minnesota tonight. Please drive slowly and with
caution if roads are slippery.

* WHAT...One to two inches of snow, with a light glazing of ice
possible.

* WHERE...Rice, Goodhue, Steele and Freeborn Counties.

* WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST TUESDAY
